This paper deals with the problem of ensuring privacy while still providing useful electronic data sources, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an analytical framework for quantifying the trade-off between privacy and utility, which involves techniques from database management (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
